race.comment: LITTLEBIRDIE (2) has had two runs back and can improve quickly over the longer trip. Gives away starts but her best numbers stack right up. KIMONO (6) peaks and was back on track beaten 1L at Echuca. An inside barrier should be advantageous, and she has claims. LITTLE RICHIE TURF (9) would be a hope on his big effort this track/trip two back. Has a handy gate and winning rider Hefel is reunited. CUDMORE STREET (1) has just one success to his name but has recorded five minor placings from 15 starts. Last start finished fourth over 2200m at this track. Include. MRS GOSSIP (12) is struggling this preparation but could add value to betting.
